==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: hootenanny
<hw>hoot"en*an*ny</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An informal social
gathering or concert featuring mostly folk songs, sometimes dancing, and
where the audience often participates in the singing.</def>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Same as <er>whatchamacallit</er>; a
thingumbob.</def> <mark>[Obsolescent, chiefly dial.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hooter</ent>⟦br⟧
